To define project specific syntaxes, just add  project_syntaxes  to your project file.   project_syntaxes  is an array; just add your syntax rules to  project_syntaxes  just like you would add them to  syntaxes  in your user settings file, and ApplySyntax will append the rules to the end of your globally defined rules.  There is one difference between project specific rules and global rules.  In project rules, the  extensions  key will be ignored, as the extension feature adds extensions globally, and project specific rules are meant to be confined to the project scope.       project_syntaxes :   [ 
         { 
             name :   XML/XML , 
             rules :   [ 
                 { file_name :   .*\\.xml(\\.dist)?$ }, 
                 { first_line :   ^ \\?xml } 
             ] 
         } 
     ]
